{ Mr. Bateman}has been making {furniture}for 17 years. He now works in a barn next to the house and employs two people. One is the son of a local farmer and the other comes from Scotland.
Most of his designs are original but there are a few chair{designs}that he repeats. Six of his{chairs}are in {national museums. { He only uses English timber and mostly uses straight pieces of wood, not curved. He has made many pieces of furniture for our house.
He recently made a high chair for{ {Prince William}and in 1984 he made a new high table and chairs for{Pembroke {College, Oxford.}
